68. Construct a PHP script that catches a division by zero error using try-catch.
 <?php
function divide($a, $b) {
    try {
        if ($b == 0) {
            throw new Exception("Division by zero not allowed.");
        }
        return $a / $b;
    } catch (Exception $e) {
        return "Error: " . $e->getMessage();
    }
}
// Test
echo divide(10, 2) . "<br>";
echo divide(10, 0); 
?>
Output:
5
Error: Division by zero not allowed.
